=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Tour_of_UGens_ex13 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark gritty sound, with noise oscillator character around 1330 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, energy distribution is late, and filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: moderate
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: gritty
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: late

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 1329.9806
  harmonic_decay_rate: -3.4077
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9016
  pitch_clarity: 177.7396
  inharmonicity: 0.1373
  type: noise
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -19.2100
  resonance_freq: 796.7285

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Tour of UGens Example 13
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Tour_of_UGens.html
// Tags: Tour_of_UGens, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 13 ---
{ FSinOsc.ar(800,0,0.1) }.play;
// FSinOsc should not be frequency modulated.
// Since it is based on a filter at the edge of stability, it will blow up:
{ FSinOsc.ar(FSinOsc.kr(FSinOsc.kr(0.2,0,8,10),0, 400,800),0,0.1) }.play;
